``python\nclass Solution:\n    def separateDigits(self, nums: List[int]) -> List[int]:\n        \n```\n\n### Answer: (use the provided format with backticks)\n", "response": "```python\nclass Solution:\n    def separateDigits(self, nums: List[int]) -> List[int]:\n        ans = []\n        for x in nums:\n            t = []\n            while x:\n                t.append(x % 10)\n                x //= 10\n            ans.extend(t[::-1])\n        return ans\n```\n\nThis solution iterates through each number in the input list `nums`, separates its digits, and appends them to the result list `ans` in the correct order. The digits of each number are extracted by repeatedly taking the remainder when divided by 10 (to get the last digit) and then performing integer division by 10 (to remove the last digit). The digits are collected in reverse order, so they are reversed before being added to `ans`.", "estimated_date": 1674950400000}